          <p>Administration &amp; Procurement Team is in charge of constructing and managing the annual plans for drilling operations and 
rotation of engineers, formulating a training program to improve drilling technologies, procuring equipments and labor, and 
other administrative work such as supporting contracts.</p> 
 <p>With regards to procuring experts and labor for drilling operations, Administration &amp; Procurement Team considers the 
drilling schedule of domestic or overseas operations, drilling capacity, and methods to formulate a systemic plan to employ 
the most suitable technicians for each project.</p>
 <p>Drilling technology has been developed rapidly in the recent years, and the drilling conditions are becoming more complicated 
and diversified, thus requiring the research and development of new drilling technologies.  In view of such, Administration 
&amp; Procurement Team is devising and operating the training programs based on each engineer¡¯s experience, knowledge, and 
expertise to enhance our drilling technology to the extent of globally recognized standard and competitive level within a 
short period of time.</p>
 <p>A well-timed supply of resources and personnel is essential to maximize the efficiency in drilling operations. Administration 
&amp; Procurement Team dispatches procurement specialists to support drilling operations by selecting and establishing supply 
bases, acquiring customs clearance for drilling equipments, and supplying the required resources and personnel.  Furthermore, 
the team conducts purchases of various equipments as well as contracting of service supplies and other contract support or 
contract management activities related to the operation.  </p> </td>
